snippet.textDisplay:
Cowboys blew enough games to show how over rated they were, now we know how mediocre they are !
I did not see the Eagles QB Wentz to lead the team to enough wins but he did play well enough even with the injuries they had on offense !
Congrats Eagles and fans , they are a beat up team so good luck !
The NFL East schedule was tough on all the teams in the East for 2019 !
I cannot explain why the wins came so few in this division !
The Giants have had a really bad 3 years no matter who they played ?
The Redskins have 3 years of QBs going on IR with broken legs ?
Dallas has no such excuses !
The Eagles should be 7-9 instead of 9-7 but QB Wentz played well enough to win more than expected with all the offensive injuries on OL and recievers and RBs ?

Next year will be very interesting for the NFC East !

snippet.textDisplay: Skip was high on Dallas when they beat the Giants and Redskins and Miami to start the season, then says the Eagles wins over the Giants and Redskins at the end of the season don't matter?  C'mon Skip, you cherry pickin' over here now.  The Eagles have proven themselves to be a better TEAM than Dallas this season.  They win the games when the games matter most, unlike Dallas that can only win at Jerryworld when all their starters are healthy and their opponent is .500 or below.  The Eagles were down to an undrafted midget at running back on Sunday and still got a TD from him.  Philly is better as an organization, and it shows in results like wins and losses, not garbage time passing yards like Dak puts up.  Sip on some Henny now Skip, you've earned it this season.
